{
  "_comment": "Two kinds of mapping. `backend`/`frontend` map a project's STACK (CLAUDE.md §5) to build skills — pass leaf keys to bootstrap, and the matching build agent invokes them only when the stack is present. Backend keys are mutually exclusive (a project has one): .net | supabase | firebase. Frontend keys coexist (a project may ship several): web | ios | flutter. `roles` maps each PIPELINE AGENT to always-on skills it uses regardless of stack — pass `roles` to install them all, or an agent name (e.g. designer) for one. Run `bash scripts/bootstrap.sh <key…>`. kind=skills-cli → `npx skills add <ref>`; kind=plugin → `claude plugin marketplace add <marketplace>` then `claude plugin install <plugin>@<marketplaceName>`; kind=mcp → configured as an MCP server, not installed here (informational). CAUTION: refs point at third-party repos tracking their default branch — they are not version-pinned (the installers do not support commit pins), so upstream renames/deletions break installs; bootstrap.sh reports any failure explicitly.",
  "backend": {
    ".net": [
      {
        "name": "dotnet-clean-arch",
        "kind": "skills-cli",
        "ref": "i4mjad/dotnet-clean-arch-skill",
        "invoke": "/dotnet-clean-arch"
      }
    ],
    "supabase": [
      {
        "name": "supabase",
        "kind": "skills-cli",
        "ref": "supabase/agent-skills@supabase",
        "invoke": "/supabase"
      },
      {
        "name": "supabase-postgres-best-practices",
        "kind": "skills-cli",
        "ref": "supabase/agent-skills@supabase-postgres-best-practices",
        "invoke": "/supabase-postgres-best-practices"
      }
    ],
    "firebase": [
